{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-article-js","path":"/scribblefall-the-new-castlefall-77893","result":{"data":{"publications":{"publication":{"metadata":{"authors":{"references":[{"id":"77896"}]},"title":"Scribblefall: the New Castlefall","description":"Castlefall is a popular word game at Mathcamp that is a mix between the games Castle of the Devil and Spyfall. This past Friday, campers invented a new version: Scribblefall. It's a refreshing variation that's just as fun as the original!"}},"extra":{"html":"<div><header class=\"page-head\" role=\"banner\"></header><main class=\"wrapper wrapper--article\" role=\"main\"><article class=\"article-content\"><header class=\"article-content__header\"><div class=\"head\"><h1 class=\"head__title\">Scribblefall: the New Castlefall</h1><p class=\"head__lead\"></p><div class=\"head__meta\"><span>Eleni Persinger</span><span>,</span> <span>7/18/21</span></div></div></header><div class=\"article-content__body\"><main class=\"article-content__main\"><figure class=\"image\"><img src=\"https://server.livingdocs.io/api/v1/images/image.png?id=MQkvMjAyMS83LzE5L2RjNjUwNjdhLWI5YzItNGMyMi04NWM1LWQ4MmMzMmRmOTBlNy5wbmcJMTM3NQ%3D%3D&rect=0%2C0%2C604%2C679&w=1024&auto=format\" srcset=\"https://server.livingdocs.io/api/v1/images/image.png?id=MQkvMjAyMS83LzE5L2RjNjUwNjdhLWI5YzItNGMyMi04NWM1LWQ4MmMzMmRmOTBlNy5wbmcJMTM3NQ%3D%3D&rect=0%2C0%2C604%2C679&w=2048&auto=format 2048w,https://server.livingdocs.io/api/v1/images/image.png?id=MQkvMjAyMS83LzE5L2RjNjUwNjdhLWI5YzItNGMyMi04NWM1LWQ4MmMzMmRmOTBlNy5wbmcJMTM3NQ%3D%3D&rect=0%2C0%2C604%2C679&w=1024&auto=format 1024w,https://server.livingdocs.io/api/v1/images/image.png?id=MQkvMjAyMS83LzE5L2RjNjUwNjdhLWI5YzItNGMyMi04NWM1LWQ4MmMzMmRmOTBlNy5wbmcJMTM3NQ%3D%3D&rect=0%2C0%2C604%2C679&w=620&auto=format 620w,https://server.livingdocs.io/api/v1/images/image.png?id=MQkvMjAyMS83LzE5L2RjNjUwNjdhLWI5YzItNGMyMi04NWM1LWQ4MmMzMmRmOTBlNy5wbmcJMTM3NQ%3D%3D&rect=0%2C0%2C604%2C679&w=320&auto=format 320w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><figcaption class=\"image__caption\"><em>An absolutely phenomenal sign created by Albert Wang for Scribblefall’s premiere this past Saturday.</em></figcaption></figure><p>You may have heard of Castlefall, a popular word game at Mathcamp that is a mix between the Castle of the Devil and Spyfall. This past Friday, campers invented a new version: Scribblefall. Scribblefall is a refreshing variation on the original that is just&nbsp;as fun¹!<br></p><p>The standard Castlefall game involves two teams, where each team has a designated secret word from a public list. Each player is given a word that decides their team, but players do not know who is on their team, or the word of the other team. The goal of the game is to either correctly guess the other team’s word or guess two other players on your own team. To do this, players discuss and often give cryptic or subtle clues to indicate their word to others on their team, but not those on the opposite team.<br></p><p>First suggested by Kevin Wu, in Scribblefall, players draw on a shared whiteboard instead of speaking or writing clues. Clues take many forms, such as this interpretation of the word limousine:<br></p><figure class=\"image\"><img src=\"https://server.livingdocs.io/api/v1/images/limousine.jpg?id=MQkvMjAyMS83LzE5LzYxMmRiNjQxLTY3YzItNDU0ZS05YzFiLWI2NGQyNTM1NTU5NS5qcGVnCTEzNzU%3D&rect=0%2C0%2C1152%2C428&w=1024&auto=format\" srcset=\"https://server.livingdocs.io/api/v1/images/limousine.jpg?id=MQkvMjAyMS83LzE5LzYxMmRiNjQxLTY3YzItNDU0ZS05YzFiLWI2NGQyNTM1NTU5NS5qcGVnCTEzNzU%3D&rect=0%2C0%2C1152%2C428&w=2048&auto=format 2048w,https://server.livingdocs.io/api/v1/images/limousine.jpg?id=MQkvMjAyMS83LzE5LzYxMmRiNjQxLTY3YzItNDU0ZS05YzFiLWI2NGQyNTM1NTU5NS5qcGVnCTEzNzU%3D&rect=0%2C0%2C1152%2C428&w=1024&auto=format 1024w,https://server.livingdocs.io/api/v1/images/limousine.jpg?id=MQkvMjAyMS83LzE5LzYxMmRiNjQxLTY3YzItNDU0ZS05YzFiLWI2NGQyNTM1NTU5NS5qcGVnCTEzNzU%3D&rect=0%2C0%2C1152%2C428&w=620&auto=format 620w,https://server.livingdocs.io/api/v1/images/limousine.jpg?id=MQkvMjAyMS83LzE5LzYxMmRiNjQxLTY3YzItNDU0ZS05YzFiLWI2NGQyNTM1NTU5NS5qcGVnCTEzNzU%3D&rect=0%2C0%2C1152%2C428&w=320&auto=format 320w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><figcaption class=\"image__caption\"><em>The first image clues the word \"limit\" (often abbreviated as \"lim\"), while the second clues \"not the cosine function,\" indicating sine. Thus, we have \"lim\" and \"sine,\" cluing \"limousine.\"</em><br></figcaption></figure><p>Drawings aren’t limited to math, however. From unintelligible doodles to angry stick figures to the flag of Malawi, the limits to one’s clues are endless. The challenge is to draw creatively, yet cryptically!<br></p><p>Though in its early stages, Scribblefall has the potential to become just as popular as Castlefall². If you haven’t had a chance to try one or both of these games yet, be on the lookout for events on the schedule board! New players are always welcome (and encouraged!) to come learn these two very exciting word games!<br></p><p>¹ In my humble opinion</p><p>² projected popularity by the end of week 5<br></p></main><aside class=\"article-content__sidebar\"><div><div class=\"placeholder--free-html\"></div></div><div><h2 class=\"sidebar-title\">Most Popular</h2><div class=\"placeholder--teaser-card\"><div class=\"teaser-card teaser-card--sidebar\"><span class=\"teaser-card__flag\">News Reporting and Trends</span><h2 class=\"teaser-card__title\"><a href=\"5-things-you-didn-t-know-about-our-collective-slack-usage-77769\">5 things you didn’t know about our collective Slack usage</a></h2><ul class=\"teaser-card__byline\"><li>by <a href=\"allison-77782\">Allison </a></li><li>Last Sunday at 8:19 PM</li></ul></div></div><div class=\"placeholder--teaser-card\"><div class=\"teaser-card teaser-card--sidebar\"><span class=\"teaser-card__flag\">Arts, Culture, and Mathematics</span><h2 class=\"teaser-card__title\"><a href=\"mathcampers-cool-signs-ppreciation-77789\">MathCampers' Cool Signs ‘Ppreciatio